{
  "texts": [
    "We collect human-written English text samples, such as books, religious texts, and blog posts, to serve as gold responses (y).",
    "Since gathering humanwritten instructions for such lengthy responses is difficult and expensive, we turn to instruction backtranslation (Li et al., 2023; Köksal et al., 2023), in which an LLM is provided with a human-written text (e.g., a short story) and prompted to generate instructions (x w) that could have been followed to create that text.",
    "We further corrupt the con- straints in x w to obtain synthetically corrupted instructions (x l) for our I-ORPO alignment method.",
    "In total, Suri contains 20K single-turn examples, each consisting of a backtranslated instruction x w, corrupted instruction x l, and a human-written response y.",
    "In this section, we detail our approach to selecting high-quality text samples (§2.1) and creating backtranslated instructions (§2.2)."
  ]
}